The paper deals with computer animation, 3D printing, and optimization techniques, which are all relevant to computer graphics (cs.GR). The focus is on processing facial animations, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) techniques such as mesh segmentation and deformation analysis. The paper also mentions graph-cut optimization, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO) applications. Finally, the paper deals with the design of 3D printed parts, which is relevant to computational geometry (cs.CG).
